cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with distributed computing networks and packet transmission. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a likely category as the paper focuses on optimizing the joint communication and computation resources in distributed computing networks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a dynamic control policy for determining routes and processing locations for packets. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with optimizing the transmission of mixed cast traffic flows. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a possible category as the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed policy in terms of throughput and packet delay.
